  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1230 mg
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Finely dice @Roma tomato{1}. Peel and finely dice @kiwi{1}(peeled and finely diced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{2}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Core, deseed, and finely chop @poblano pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and finely chopped).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp} and a squeeze of lime juice. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. In a #medium bowl{}, toss together tomato, kiwi, minced shallots, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano, sliced shallots, and half the @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later). Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened and lightly charred, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @ground pork{10%ounce}, another large drizzle of oil, and remaining Mexican Spice to pan. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until pork is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Reduce heat under pan to medium low.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings), and @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}. Cook, stirring, until everything is coated in a thick sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

== Lime Crema and Kiwi Salsa ==

Combine sour cream and a squeeze of lime juice in a small bowl. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

In a medium bowl, toss together tomato, kiwi, minced shallots, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Divide between plates and top with pork filling, salsa, and crema. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.